Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph wikg://local/job add --input <chapter-uri|archive-uri>

Purpose:
  Create generation tasks for one `.wikg` chapter or every buildable chapter in an archive.

Usage:
  wikigraph wikg://local/job add --input <chapter-uri|archive-uri> --task <reading-graph|reading-summary|knowledge-graph> --accept-cost [--boost] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>] [--json]

Options:
  --input <uri>        Chapter URI for one job, or archive URI for all buildable chapters.
  --task <task>        Required task: reading-graph, reading-summary, or knowledge-graph.
  --accept-cost        Explicitly acknowledge LLM cost and wait time.
  --boost              Insert the new job at the front of the queued jobs.
  --llm <json>         Override LLM configuration for this job.
  --prompt <text>      Override extraction prompt for this job.
  --json               Print created jobs as JSON.

Task choices:
  reading-graph        Build the reading-oriented chunk graph from sourced text.
  reading-summary      Build summaries from the Reading Graph. Builds reading-graph first when needed.
  knowledge-graph      Build entity mentions from sourced text. Required before entity search can return results.

Merge rules:
  - Source is required first; wikg://local/job add does not create or import source text.
  - knowledge-graph requires `wikg://local/config/wikispine`; run `wikigraph wikg://local/config/wikispine test` before queueing.
  - Archive input skips planned chapters.
  - reading-graph and reading-summary share one Reading Graph lane job per chapter.
  - Adding reading-summary upgrades an active reading-graph job for the same chapter.
  - knowledge-graph uses a separate lane and can run alongside the Reading Graph lane for the same chapter.

Examples:
  wikigraph wikg://local/job add --input wikg://book.wikg/chapter/3 --task reading-graph --accept-cost
  wikigraph wikg://local/job add --input wikg://book.wikg --task knowledge-graph --accept-cost
  wikigraph wikg://local/job add --input wikg://book.wikg/chapter/3 --task reading-summary --accept-cost --boost
  wikigraph wikg://local/job add --input wikg://book.wikg/chapter/3 --task knowledge-graph --accept-cost
